FT  15 OCT 93 / Man remanded in Pounds 1.7m VAT case
MR MICHAEL ROWAN, who was charged on Wednesday with evading payment of
Pounds 1.7m of value added tax, was yesterday remanded on bail of Pounds
90,000 at City Magistrates Court in London.
Customs and Excise investigations division, prosecuting, told magistrates
that Mr Rowan, of Hampton, Middlesex, contravened section 39 (3) of the 1983
VAT Act - which deals with VAT evasion - between October 12 1990 and October
13 this year, at Cardinal House, Northfields Avenue, Ealing, London, and
elsewhere in England and Wales.
The case was adjourned for three months.
